â—ï¸ wc -b is invalid â€” use -c for byte count.

ğŸ§¾ Count from Command Output
ğŸ“„ Count Files in a Directory
bash
Copy
Edit
ls -l | wc -l
Includes the total line, so subtract 1:

bash
Copy
Edit
expr $(ls -l | wc -l) - 1
ğŸ“ Count Only Directories
bash
Copy
Edit
ls -l | grep '^d' | wc -l
^d = lines starting with d (i.e. directories)

Skips the total line automatically

ğŸ§  Optional exercise: Try find . -type d | wc -l to count subdirectories recursively.

ğŸ” Count Matching Lines with grep
bash
Copy
Edit
grep "Seinfeld" seinfeld-characters | wc -l
Counts how many lines match "Seinfeld"

ğŸ’¡ Pro Tips
Combine wc with grep, ls, or cat for insights

Always check wc --help or man wc for detailed options

Use awk or cut if you need to count specific fields

